    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Another workaround would be to _skip_ the long-running jobs on pull requests, then run them only on the merge queue.\r\n\r\nI was having a poke around some other people's workflow YAML to see what they do, and it seems this is a common approach, e.g.\r\n\r\n- `determine` job to calculate what to run: https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/85cbaa5220fd4028dfc5203171ebd92375949d16/.github/workflows/main.yml#L110-L120\r\n- `status` job to report a unified status based on everything that did run: https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/85cbaa5220fd4028dfc5203171ebd92375949d16/.github/workflows/main.yml#L661-L713",
